@sharkdentures3247 You're misremembering a lot of things. As a Gen Xer, I guarantee you that most of the female celebrities you grew up with, and before your time, either died young, quickly turned to intensive vanity to stave off the ravages of old age, or retired and withdrew into shells of their former glory. Which is easy to misremember when you didn't have the internet in those days to feed you daily reminders of how insane and vain the women of those days were.
Most of the women in those days were also kept in check by studio fixers, like Eddie Mannix, whose sole job was to maintain a squeaky clean image for them. Back in the days when PR could literally backhand a celebrity if they toed out of line.

Celebrities today are just the same as they were 20, 30, 40, even 50+ years ago. The internet has only broken down the illusions that kept so many people mystified in blissful ignorance of what really went on behind the scenes.

@RSvids1012 This is a matter of taste. Scarlet is more conventionally beautiful, while Sydney has a very specific look with her dreamy eyes. Don't forget, Miss Johansson also had a breast reduction surgery at some point, so she was actually not too far behind in that department either before doing so, for the men of culture that care.

